STEP 6 : CONSTRUCTOR EXECUTES
====================================================

this.name = name;

Copies the constructor parameter
into the object's field.

this.age = age;

Now Heap becomes

Student Object

name -----> "Aditya"
age = 28

The String "Aditya" comes from the String Pool
(or is created there if not already present).

====================================================
STEP 7 : CONSTRUCTOR RETURNS
====================================================

Constructor finishes.

Its Stack Frame is popped.

Stack

main()

s1 -----> Student Object

Control returns to main().

====================================================
STEP 8 : CALL

s1.markAttendance()
====================================================

Since this is an instance method,

JVM first finds

s1 ---> Student Object

Then creates another Stack Frame.

Stack

markAttendance()

main()

Inside markAttendance(),

the hidden variable

this

points to the Student object.

System.out.println(name);

actually becomes

System.out.println(this.name);

Output

Aditya is present

Method finishes.

Stack becomes

main()

====================================================
STEP 9 : CALL STATIC METHOD

Student.changeCollege("IIT Bombay");
====================================================

Since this is STATIC,

no object is required.

JVM directly looks inside the Method Area.

Method Area

Student

changeCollege()

A new Stack Frame is created.

Stack

changeCollege()

main()

Execution

college = "IIT Bombay";

The static variable is updated.

Method Area

Student

college -----> "IIT Bombay"

The old String "IIT G" becomes unreachable
(if nothing references it).

====================================================
STEP 10 : MAIN FINISHES
====================================================

main() reaches the end.

The main Stack Frame is removed.

Stack

(empty)

The reference s1 disappears.

Now no live reference points to the Student object.

The object becomes eligible for Garbage Collection.

====================================================
IMPORTANT INTERVIEW POINTS
====================================================

1. "new" does TWO things:

- Allocates memory in Heap.
- Invokes the constructor.

----------------------------------------------------

2. Constructor is just another method.

It gets its own Stack Frame.

----------------------------------------------------

3. Instance methods require an object.

JVM uses the object reference to execute them.

----------------------------------------------------

4. Static methods belong to the class.

They do not require any object.

They are resolved using class metadata stored in the Method Area.

----------------------------------------------------

5. Every method call creates a new Stack Frame.

Example

main()

↓

Student()

↓

markAttendance()

↓

println()

Each method gets its own frame.

----------------------------------------------------

6. Every thread has:

- One Stack
- One Program Counter

Each method call pushes a new Stack Frame.

----------------------------------------------------

7. Heap stores actual objects.

Stack stores only references to those objects.

----------------------------------------------------

8. Method Area stores:

- Class metadata
- Method definitions
- Constructor definitions
- Static variables
- Runtime Constant Pool

